item.dc:creator: @Shorty626 Shorty626

item.title: Java help
item.dc:creator: @deathschaos9 DeathsChaos9
item.description:
@deathschaos9 wrote:

First try changing the path of Java from JRE to JDK or vice versa and try to run the client. If neither of them work, download 32-bit Java even if you have a 64-bit OS.

Read full topic

item.title: Java help
item.dc:creator: @Epic_Steve Epic Steve
item.description:
@Epic_Steve wrote:

Access violations are due to programs accessing memory addresses that the operating system did not assign the program to.

In some cases these can be resolved by uninstalling the JVM doing a registry cleanup and reinstalling.

Read full topic
